==English==

===Noun===
'''twin''' (''plural:'' [[twins]])

#One of two people (or, less commonly, animals) who shared the same [[uterus]] at the same time. Can be [[dizygotic]], i.e., coming from different [[fertilized]] [[ova]] ([[zygote]]s), or [[monozygotic]], from one zygote that divided into two at some point during its development. Monozygotic twins are more commonly known as [[identical]] twins, and dizogotic as [[fraternal]] twins.

